Package edu.temple.vrl.biofilm_evaluator

Class BatchProcessing

java.lang.Object
edu.temple.vrl.biofilm_evaluator.BatchProcessing
public class BatchProcessing
extends java.lang.Object
Class containing useful helper methods for batch processing of biofilm data. Requires a specific naming convention for mesh and image stack files.

    • printRatio

      public static void printRatio​(int num30000, int num60000, double vol30000, double vol60000, java.lang.String import_filename, java.lang.String export_filename) throws java.io.IOException
      Creates a new .csv file and prints to it certain useful quantities such as the ratio of the number of structures of the same biofilm at two different thresholds or the ratio between the volume of the same biofilm at two different thresholds.
      Parameters:
      num30000 - number of distinct structures at threshold 30000.
      num60000 - number of distinct structures at threshold 60000.
      vol30000 - total volume at threshold 30000
      vol60000 - total volume at threshold 60000
      import_filename - name of file evaluated
      export_filename - name of file exported
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - file not found
